main event: A conical-shaped object was observed moving from left to right across the sky over San Jose, California for about 5-10 seconds.
interesting points: The object was approximately one-fourth the size of the moon or less.
The object had a long trail and appeared to glide sharply to the right and turn towards the southeast.
The sighting occurred at around 8:33 PM local time on December 24, 1963.
The witness was a naval aviation lieutenant commander who was also a civilian minister.
The sighting was reported to the Project Blue Book program.
sighted object: Conical-shaped object with a long trail
